commText: Jaiswal and Buttler are at the crease. Jaiswal is on strike. Hardik Pandya will open the attack
Hardik Pandya to Jaiswal, no run, 133.7kph, away-angling length ball, not much bounce outside off and Jaiswal shoulders arms
Hardik Pandya to Jaiswal, 1 run, 132.6kph, strays onto the pads does Pandya and that's been glanced to fine leg
Hardik Pandya to Buttler, no run, 131.4kph, inswinger, good length on off, tapped into the off-side

Hardik Pandya to Buttler, FOUR, 136.2kph, Hardik goes full and bowls an outswinger outside off. Buttler reaches out to drive and the bottom hand comes off. Not quite off the middle of the bat but enough wood on it to clear mid-off

Hardik Pandya to Buttler, FOUR, 136.5kph,, back-to-back boundaries! On a length and wide of off, Buttler check-drives and the bottom hand comes off the bat handle. However, the timing is good on it. Uppish but in the gap through the covers. Hardik can't believe it...
Hardik Pandya to Buttler, 2 runs, 138.1kph, opens the bat-face to steer this length ball to deep backward point
Jasprit Bumrah, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Bumrah to Jaiswal, 1 run, 134.4kph, Jaiswal hangs back, waits for this short of length ball and runs it down to third man
This should be fun - Bumrah vs Buttler! One slip in place
Bumrah to Buttler, no run, 123.4kph, pace off, very full, Buttler spots it late and pushes it back to the bowler

Bumrah to Buttler, no run, 136.5kph, in-angler that seams back in sharply, no room on offer, Buttler stays in his crease to flick and gets hit high on the back thigh. Bumrah appeals but MI don't review. Too high
Bumrah to Buttler, no run, stays back to push this length ball to cover
Bumrah to Buttler, 1 run, outswinger, full in length, Buttler push-drives to cover and a misfield allows the batters to rotate strike

Bumrah to Jaiswal, no run, 143.1kph, low full toss outside off, Jaiswal drives sans any feet movement and the outside edge goes towards first slip on the bounce. Tidy opening over from Bumrah, no risks taken by the RR openers
Here's the debutant!
Nuwan Thushara, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
N Thushara to Buttler, 1 run, starts with a low full toss on the stumps and Buttler clips it away to deep square leg
N Thushara to Jaiswal, 1 run, 132.5kph, inswinging yorker, Jaiswal brings his bat down just in time and squeezes it out towards short third man
N Thushara to Buttler, 1 run, 118.8kph, off-speed full delivery, Buttler stays in his crease and is early to drive, inside-edges to midwicket
N Thushara to Jaiswal, 1 run, 131.9kph, short of a good length, shapes in towards leg and that's been flicked to deep backward square leg

N Thushara to Buttler, 1 run, edged! 134.8kph, Buttler sees the width and slashes hard for a cut. Gets it off the toe-end of the bat and beats Bumrah's dive to his right at short third man. Deep backward point cuts it off
N Thushara to Jaiswal, 1 run, 121.1kph, pace off, length ball, knocked towards mid-on. Six balls and six singles
Gerald Coetzee, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Gerald Coetzee to Jaiswal, SIX, 140.1kph, Jaiswal greets Gerald Coetzee with a six. Fuller than a length, Jaiswal shuffles across and thumps it downtown for a maximum. Clean strike!
Gerald Coetzee to Jaiswal, no run, 147.8kph, good comeback from Coetzee. Hits the deck hard as he pulls his length back. Jaiswal flashes hard and misses!
Gerald Coetzee to Jaiswal, no run, 149.9kph! In-slanting shortish ball, Jaiswal arches his back to try and cheekily dab it away, beaten on the outside edge
Gerald Coetzee to Jaiswal, wide, 140.7kph, short of length down leg, Jaiswal lets it be and Kishan moves to his right to pouch it
Gerald Coetzee to Jaiswal, no run, 146.6kph, short of a length ball around off, Jaiswal defends from the crease

Gerald Coetzee to Jaiswal, FOUR, 149.4kph, streaky boundary. Too quick for the left-hander, Jaiswal got into a tangle there. The line was spot-on as well from Coetzee who bowled a superb bouncer. Jaiswal is clearly late on the pull and fortunately for him, the top-edge flies over the keeper
Gerald Coetzee to Jaiswal, wide, attempts the slower ball and errs with his line - way outside off

Gerald Coetzee to Jaiswal, FOUR, 151.1kph! Classy shot from Jaiswal. Pacy back of a length outside off, Jaiswal waits for it, stands tall on the back foot and punches into the gap through the covers. 16 runs off the eventful over!
Jasprit Bumrah [1.0-0-2-0] is back into the attack
Bumrah to Buttler, no run, 130.1kph, off-cutter from Bumrah, Buttler doesn't pick it and is early into his drive. The ball goes past inside edge and misses the off-stump by a whisker
Bumrah to Buttler, FOUR, 143kph, pace on, short in length and Buttler pulls it away in front of square on the leg-side. Doesn't over-hit and hits it in the gap
Bumrah to Buttler, 1 run, 125.2kph, slower delivery, knocked towards mid-on for a quick single
Bumrah to Jaiswal, no run, blocked back to the bowler
Bumrah to Jaiswal, no run, 138.2kph, short of length on off, punched to extra cover
Bumrah to Jaiswal, FOUR, 139.5kph, Bumrah slightly overpitches outside off and Jaiswal punishes. A confident stride forward from the left-hander and he drives sweetly through extra cover
Nuwan Thushara [1.0-0-6-0] is back into the attack
N Thushara to Buttler, no run, length ball on off, driven towards extra cover

N Thushara to Buttler, FOUR, Buttler takes the aerial route. 118.5kph, pace off on a short of length, Buttler waits on the back foot and punches it over the covers. A couple of fidlers chase but the quick outfield does its job
N Thushara to Buttler, FOUR, hits through the line. 121.6kph, slower ball on a length, Buttler spots it and smashes it over mid-off. Fifty partnership between Buttler and Jaiswal! Great signs for RR!
N Thushara to Buttler, 1 run, 137.7kph, pace on and in the blockhole, jammed towards mid-on
Stat: First 50+ opening partnership between Jaiswal and Buttler this season

N Thushara to Jaiswal, FOUR, 138.1kph, Thushara misses his yorker and ends up bowling a low full toss outside off. Jaiswal latches onto it. Driven firmly between point and cover. Bullets away to the fence

N Thushara to Jaiswal, FOUR, 119.3kph, slow and full outside off, Jaiswal drives to the right of mid-off and Hardik dives over the ball. Not a great effort from the skipper and the ball dribbles away to the fence. 17 runs off the final over of the powerplay!

Powerplay summary -- Superb start from the RR openers -- Hardik opens the attack, goes for 11 in 1st over -- Bumrah, Thushara bowl tight first overs -- Coetzee bowls over 150kph, but is taken for runs -- Jaiswal doesn't go ultra-aggressive for a change, and finds his timing again

Strategic timeout! Rajasthan are off to a flier. This is their best opening stand of the season. Bumrah has already bowled a couple of overs. Can MI find a way to exert some sort of pressure? If not, RR will romp home

22:05 Local Time, 16:35 GMT, 22:05 IST: Oops! It has started raining and the covers are coming on. DLS par score at this stage is 41, so RR are well ahead. But hopefully it won't come down to that. The rain isn't too heavy at the moment.
22:20 Local Time, 16:50 GMT, 22:20 IST: Rain has stopped and covers are being taken off. Play to resume at 10.33pm local.
22:33 Local Time, 17:03 GMT, 22:33 IST: Looks like there is a further delay. The drizzle has returned.
There will be an inspection at 10.45pm local.. Covers are being taken off again.
22:41 Local Time, 17:11 GMT, 22:41 IST: So the latest is that play will resume at 10.45pm local. Inspection must've happened already and the umpires are happy with conditions. No overs lost.
All set to go again. Nabi has the ball.
Mohammad Nabi, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Nabi to Buttler, 1 run, 88.3kph, tossed up outside off, Buttler gets forward and drives to long-off
Nabi to Jaiswal, FOUR, tossed up on off, overpitched and Jaiswal crunches it through extra cover. He clears the front leg and absolutely nails the drive to the boundary
Nabi to Jaiswal, 1 run, 84.3kph, length ball outside off, Jaiswal stretches forward and plays a flat-batted drive to sweeper cover
Nabi to Buttler, 1 run, flat length ball on middle and leg, Buttler hangs back and tucks it behind square
Nabi to Jaiswal, no run, grip and turn for Nabi! Tossed up on off, draws Jaiswal forward in defence but dips and goes past the outside edge. Cracking delivery!
Nabi to Jaiswal, no run, full on off, pushed to short cover
Piyush Chawla, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Chawla to Buttler, 1 run, overpitched on off, Buttler looks to drive and drags it off the inside half through midwicket
Chawla to Jaiswal, 1 run, flat length ball on off, googly, Jaiswal hangs back and punches to sweeper cover

Chawla to Buttler, no run, oh sharp turn again! Nabi got one to rip in the previous over, now Chawla's turn! Tossed up around middle, Buttler goes for a big slog but it rips past the outside edge. Kishan is impressed as he gathers
Chawla to Buttler, no run, goes for a reverse-sweep, it's a googly tossed up outside off, and Buttler finds short third
Chawla to Buttler, FOUR, full ball on middle, Buttler goes for the reverse-sweep again and this time he finds the gap! Cracks it away through point for four!
Chawla to Buttler, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Chawla to Buttler, out Bowled!! Chawla breaks the partnership! Skiddy googly on off, Buttler looks to pull but it doesn't get up as much as he expects. The ball sneaks through and crashes into off stump. Buttler b Chawla 35(25) [4s-6]
Sanju Samson, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Nabi to Jaiswal, no run, drifting in on leg from round the wicket, Jaiswal looks to defend forward and gets an inside edge onto pad
Nabi to Jaiswal, 1 run, good stuff from both these MI spinners after the break. Tossed up on off, Jaiswal gets forward and knocks it through point
Nabi to Samson, 1 run, flat outside off, back of a length, Samson goes back and punches through cover
Nabi to Jaiswal, no run, length ball sliding in on off, Jaiswal hangs back and punches to short cover

Nabi to Jaiswal, SIX, there was a bit of pressure building and Jaiswal's response is to step out and whack one for six! Tossed up on off, he shows excellent footwork, gets right to the pitch of it and launches it down the ground
Stat: This is now the highest score of the season for Jaiswal
Nabi to Jaiswal, 1 run, length ball on off, Jaiswal gets forward and knocks it through point
Chawla to Jaiswal, no run, googly on middle, length ball, Jaiswal hangs back and knocks it back to Chawla
Chawla to Jaiswal, FOUR, sloppy from Nabi at the boundary! Slightly short outside off, Jaiswal waits on it and cuts nicely through backward point. Should've been cut off in the deep

Chawla to Jaiswal, 1 run, knocks this googly to long-on, raises his fifty and blows a kiss to the dugout! It's his first fifty of the season as he puts a stop to his lean run. Instead of going ultra-aggressive at the start, like he had been doing, he took a bit of time today and focussed on the timing
Chawla to Samson, 1 run, punched off the back foot to long-off
Chawla to Jaiswal, no run, defended to point

Chawla to Jaiswal, SIX, Wadhera has made an absolute mess of this opportunity. Wasn't that difficult a chance at the long-off boundary, but he pedals back, loses his balance and loses the ball as well. Googly on off, Jaiswal dances down to go for a lofted shot but loses his shape as he swings very hard. Ends up miscuing it in the air off the outside half, but gets away with it
Nabi to Samson, no run, defended
Nabi to Samson, 1 run, knocks this one down to long-off
Nabi to Jaiswal, SIX, length ball sliding in on off Jaiswal gets down on one knee and nails the slog-sweep over the midwicket boundary
Nabi to Jaiswal, leg byes, 1 run, length ball sliding down leg, Jaiswal looks to glance but it goes off his pad to short fine
Nabi to Samson, SIX, flat on middle and leg, not all that short, but Samson goes back and pulls it brilliantly. Goes for a flat six over deep midwicket who tries his best but fails to get a hand
Nabi to Samson, 1 run, flat outside off, back of a length, Samson makes room and slaps it to sweeper cover
Chawla to Samson, 1 run, googly on middle and leg, length ball, Samson goes back and punches to long-on
Chawla to Jaiswal, 1 run, slightly short on off, pulled to deep midwicket
Chawla to Samson, no run, fuller than a length on middle, legbreak, Samson gets forward and defends to short cover
Chawla to Samson, no run, tossed up on off, googly, Samson clears the front leg for a lofted shot but drags it off a thick inside edge onto pad
Chawla to Samson, 1 run, length ball sliding in on leg, Samson hangs back and tucks it into the on-side
Chawla to Jaiswal, no run, length ball on off, Jaiswal hangs back and taps it to backward point

Overs 7-12 summary -- 52/1 -- Play resumes after a 40-minute rain break -- Spinners operate in tandem -- Chawla cleans up Buttler with a googly -- 31-ball fifty for Jaiswal -- Wadhera drops Jaiswal on 50 and palms it over the fence -- 15 runs off Nabi's 3rd over -- Chawla bowls a tight over
Hardik Pandya [1.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack
Hardik Pandya to Samson, 1 run, back of a length outside off, Samson cuts to deep point
Hardik Pandya to Jaiswal, 1 run, backs away a long way from the stumps, Hardik follows him, it's back of a length around the waist, Jaiswal looks to pull and gets an under-edge onto the thigh
Hardik Pandya to Samson, SIX, clobbered! Samson's turn to back away, gets a juicy slower ball in the slot and launches it over the long-on boundary with a fierce swing
Hardik Pandya to Samson, no run, back of a length outside off, slower one, Samson looks to cut but is beaten

Hardik Pandya to Samson, 1 run, would you believe this! Another catch goes down and this is an absolute sitter. Back of a length around off, slower one, Samson looks to pull and gets it high on the bat. Should've been a simple catch for David at long-on but he shells it
Hardik Pandya to Jaiswal, 1 run, length ball on off, driven to long-on
Chawla to Jaiswal, 1 run, tossed up on leg stump, Jaiswal gets on one knee and sweeps hard to deep backward square
Chawla to Samson, 1 run, length ball on off, punched to long-off

Chawla to Jaiswal, SIX, Jaiswal steps out, gets a ball fired in outside off at close to 100kph and lofts it without any trouble over the long-off boundary. Again he was able to get right to the pitch of the ball with his footwork
Chawla to Jaiswal, 2 runs, tossed up on leg, googly, Jaiswal gets low and sweeps it fine. Easy couple of runs
Chawla to Jaiswal, 1 run, googly on off, length ball, Jaiswal goes back and punches to long-off
Chawla to Samson, 1 run, length ball on off, googly, Samson punches off the back foot to long-on
Jasprit Bumrah [2.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack
Bumrah to Samson, no ball, 1 run, slower length ball on off, Samson flicks it to deep midwicket. Oh dear. The misery keeps piling for MI as Bumrah oversteps

Bumrah to Jaiswal, wide, short ball around leg stump, Jaiswal looks to pull but is beaten. It's called wide, but MI review. Third umpire finds that the ball is well above the head, so the wide call stays

Bumrah to Jaiswal, SIX, the free-hit disappears over the ropes! Slower length ball on leg, 130kph, Jaiswal clears the front leg, swings hard and makes good contact. It sails over the long leg boundary

Bumrah to Jaiswal, FOUR, short of length at the body, slower one, and Jaiswal dispatches it for four more! Gets right on top of the bounce and pulls it behind square. Such a delight to watch him bat when on song
Bumrah to Jaiswal, no run, fuller than a length outside off, driven to extra cover
Bumrah to Jaiswal, 1 run, pitched up outside off, driven to sweeper cover
Bumrah to Samson, 1 run, back of a length on off, Samson hangs back and tucks it through midwicket
Bumrah to Jaiswal, 1 run, low full toss on off, 140.9kph, Jaiswal flicks it to long-on. 16 off the Bumrah over - easily his most expensive of the season
Gerald Coetzee [1.0-0-16-0] is back into the attack
Gerald Coetzee to Jaiswal, no run, short of length outside off, slower one, Jaiswal cuts gently to backward point

Gerald Coetzee to Jaiswal, no run, immediate appeal from Kishan for caught-behind. Umpire, though, signals a wide, and MI go for the review. Short ball down leg, Jaiswal is late on the pull and is clipped on the forearm guard on its way to the keeper. The wide call will be overturned
Gerald Coetzee to Jaiswal, 2 runs, short of length outside off, Jaiswal cuts nicely through backward point, gets back for two
Gerald Coetzee to Jaiswal, wide, banged in short, Jaiswal bends under it, goes belatedly for a ramp but is beaten. Called a wide for height
Gerald Coetzee to Jaiswal, no run, back of a length outside off, slower one, Jaiswal hangs back and punches to extra cover

Gerald Coetzee to Jaiswal, no run, short of length at the body, slower one at 129kph, Jaiswal looks to pull but is deceived by the lack of pace. He's early through the shot and gets hit on the chest. Coetzee troubled him in his first over, and he's causing him more problems here
Gerald Coetzee to Jaiswal, SIX, short of length on off, 130kph, and Jaiswal climbs all over it! Goes for the pull and thumps it over the square leg boundary
Timeout!

Overs 13-16 summary -- 47/0 -- David drops Samson on 19 off Hardik's bowling -- Fifty partnership off 31 balls between Jaiswal & Samson -- Bumrah concedes 16 runs off his 3rd over -- Coetzee troubles Jaiswal but the left-hander caps off the over with a six

Bumrah to Samson, no run, yorker down leg, Samson misses, and it goes through to the keeper. Samson is puzzled by the umpire not signalling a wide and goes for a review. Third umpire says it would've struck his pad had he not moved, so the decision stays

Bumrah to Samson, FOUR, Bumrah goes for another yorker, ends up as a low full toss on the pads, and Samson flicks it away past short fine. If this man's execution is off, you can imagine how bad a night this is for MI
Bumrah to Samson, 1 run, length ball outside off, slower one, Samson waits and dabs it to deep third
Bumrah to Jaiswal, 1 run, full toss on middle, slower one, Jaiswal gets forward and drives to mid-off

Bumrah to Samson, FOUR, another poor effort from Nabi in the deep, and Bumrah breaks into a helpless smile! Full and wide, slower one, Samson reaches out and drives crisply through extra cover. Should've been cut off easily, but Nabi has trouble bending as he runs across and lets it through
Bumrah to Samson, no run, back of a length outside off, Samson leaves it alone. Rohit and Samson share a laugh about the leave
Nuwan Thushara [2.0-0-23-0] is back into the attack
N Thushara to Jaiswal, 1 run, length ball on the pads, slower one, Jaiswal clips it behind square
N Thushara to Samson, 1 run, length ball outside off, slower one again, Samson shuffles across and punches to long-off
N Thushara to Jaiswal, 1 run, full outside off, driven to long-off
N Thushara to Samson, no run, fuller than a length outside off, driven to cover
N Thushara to Samson, 1 run, length ball on off, slower one, Samson gets forward and punches it to long-on
N Thushara to Jaiswal, 1 run, slower length ball wide of off, Jaiswal advances down and flat-bats it to long-off
Tilak Varma, right-arm off break, comes into the attack

Tilak Varma to Jaiswal, 1 run, short outside off, Jaiswal cuts to sweeper cover and charges across to the other end with bat in one hand, and helmet in another. He's absolutely thrilled as he brings up his second IPL hundred - both of them coming against MI. Wasn't at his best in the tournament before this game, but has put the bowling to the sword today
Tilak Varma to Samson, 2 runs, punched wide of long-off, back for two
Tilak Varma to Samson, 1 run, bunts it to long-on for a single
13th individual century scored against MI - the joint most against an opponent alongside RCB

Tilak Varma to Jaiswal, FOUR, slightly short outside off, Jaiswal goes back and cuts it to the boundary to wrap it up! Kishan gives him a hug, Rohit congratulates him. Brilliant knock from the 22-year old to end his run of lean scores and lead his team to victory

23:47 Local Time, 18:17 GMT, 23:47 IST: Rajasthan Royals strengthen their position at the top with seven wins in eight matches. The one little wrinkle of Jaiswal not scoring runs has also been ironed out today. He looks chuffed as he gets a big hug from Jos Buttler. The two were seen having a long conversation during the rain break, and while Buttler didn't last too long after the resumption, his younger partner carried on all the way. MI's decision at the toss of batting first didn't work out the way they'd have wanted. They got the worst of the conditions, with the ball stopping in the first innings, and then coming on much better in the second as the rain came down and outfield became damp. Their fielding was shoddy as well with two chances going down, and Jaiswal made them pay heavily.

Hardik Pandya: We put ourselves in trouble early on. The way Tilak and Nehal batted - that was fantastic. I don't think that when we lost a couple of wickets early we thought we would even reach 180. We didn't finish well and that's why we were 10-15 runs short. We had to keep it within the stumps (while bowling). Early on in the powerplay, we gave a lot of width and I don't think it was our best day in the field as well. Overall, we did not put the right foot on the park and eventually they outplayed us. After the game, it's not the right time to go to the players, everyone is professional, they know their roles. What we can do is learn from this game and the mistakes which we have made, rectify it and make sure that we don't make it. Progression is very important. Within the team, individually, we will have to accept our flaws and maybe work on those. I don't believe much in chip and chop, I like to back players and the focus would always be to play good cricket, sticking to our plans and making sure that we don't make the basic errors. Cricket is simple, as long as we keep it simple, it's nice.

Yashasvi Jaiswal: Thank you so much, I really enjoyed from the start and I made sure I was watching the ball properly and playing proper cricketing shots. I’m trying to do what I am doing well, some days it comes good and some days it doesn’t, I’m not thinking much. I want to thank all my seniors the way they have guided me. I want to thank the Rajasthan Royals management and especially Sanga sir and Sanju bhai for giving me opportunities. I go out and give my best in the practice sessions and I’m so happy today.

Yashasvi Jaiswal is the first player to score two centuries in IPL before turning 23. 124 vs MI Wankhede 2023 (21y 123d) 104*vs MI Jaipur 2024 (22y 116d) Most hundred vs an opposition (IPL) 3 KL Rahul vs MI 2 C Gayle vs PBKS 2 V Kohli vs GL 2 D Warner vs KKR 2 J Buttler vs KKR 2 J Buttler vs RCB 2 Y Jaiswal vs MI Winning seven out of the first eight matches in an IPL season Mumbai Indians in 2010 Punjab Kings in 2014 Chennai Super Kings in 2019 Gujarat Titans in 2022 Rajasthan Royals in 2024 * Rajasthan Royals in Jaipur IPL 2023: One win & four defeats IPL 2024: Four wins & one defeat

Samson, RR captain: Credit has to go to all the players. Started well in the powerplay. In the middle, the left-handers played unbelievably. But the way we came back was where we won the game. Wicket looked a bit dry. But when lights come in, gets colder in the night, it gets better to bat in the second innings. People are professional enough about what to do when they get a break. I don't think he needs (advice from) anyone (Jaiswal). He's very confident. Was about one game. Let's see how the wicket is there (Lucknow) and let's see how it goes.

Sandeep, POTM: Got fit day before yesterday only. First game after fitness, feeling good. Pitch was on slower side and lower side, so my plan was to keep bowling variations and cutters. If you're bowling in the end, you have to have big heart. Have seen in the IPL, bowlers are under the pump. Need to have big heart and keep executing plans. As you know, I went unsold two years ago. Came in as a replacement. So I'm enjoying every game.

A five-for on return from injury for Sandeep Sharma, and a hundred from Yashasvi Jaiswal later in the evening. Those were two outstanding individual performances that contributed heavily to the win for RR who keep going from strength to strength. Today the decision at the toss worked in their favour as well, with MI opting to bat first. Samson, knowing the conditions, was happy with that result. And he'll be a lot more happier with the overall outcome. That's it from us here. This is Sagar Chawla signing off on behalf of Harish, Abhinand Raghavendran and Abhinav Guha. Goodbye!
